Blocks.childText: 8 Elementary Department. CHAPTER XII. MELODICS. Clefs. 79. The notation of a piece of music should be kept as much as possible with- in the long lines and spaces of the staff. Ladies' voices are higher than men's voices, and in order to represent the pitches these two classes of voices sing, the staff is made to represent pitches in two ways. When it is wanted to represent the pitch- es that ladies sing, this character, called the TREBLE CLEF, is put upon it. The staff then represents pitches as follows: The first added line below stands for the pitch C; the first space (space below) stands for pitch D; first line E; second space F; second line G; third space A; third line B; fourth space C; fourth line D; fifth space E; fifth line F; sixth space G. If we go higher, the pitches represented in regular order are, A, B, C, D, etc. The added lines and spaces below represent pitches as follows, beginning with first added line: C, B, A, G,. etc. 80. When the staff is wanted to represent the pitches that men sing, this char- acter, 9: called the BASE CLEF, is put upon it. The staff then represents pitches in the following order, beginning with the first line: G, A, B, C, D, E, F, G, A, B, C,. etc. 81. The first added line below when the treble clef is used, and the first added above when the base clef is used, represent the same pitch C, and are the centre and junctional point of the two staves. The pitch they jointly represent is about midway the male and female voices, and is called MIDDLE C. See the following EXAMPLE. 9 CHAPTER XIII. MELODICS. Keys-Key of C. 82. Every scale and tune is within some key. One of every scale is called the key-tone, and the pitch taken for the key-tone gives name to the key. Thus, if C be one, the scale or tune is in the key of C; if D be one, it is in the key of D; etc. 83. Musical instruction usually begins with the key of C. The staff is made to represent the key of C by having none of its degrees modified; thus, SCALE OF C, Treble Clef. SCALE OF C, Base Clef. Do, Re, Mi, Fa, Sol, La, Si, Do. Do, Re, Mi, Fa, Sol, La, Si, Do. 84. To make the staff represent other keys than C, one or more of its degrees must be modified.
